                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12639099" author="rhs" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2008 16:35:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe the cause of this is actually a race condition that has been around forever but gone unnoticed since the stack trace was just buried in the logs and never reported. My changes are showing this up by actually reporting the exception. I&apos;m working on a fix for the original race condition.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12639136" author="rhs" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2008 17:58:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AMQConnection.java:935 is this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                    catch (AMQException e)&lt;/p&gt;
                    {
                        JMSException jmse = new JMSException(&quot;Error closing connection: &quot; + e); &amp;lt;-------------
                        jmse.setLinkedException(e);
                        throw jmse;
                    }

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately the JMSException seems to swallow the original stack trace of the linked exception. I&apos;ve committed a change to log the original error. I can&apos;t reproduce this on my system, so hopefully the next time it shows up we have a bit more info.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12639396" author="ritchiem" created="Tue, 14 Oct 2008 11:48:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Recent failure with exception logged.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12657565" author="rgodfrey" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2008 21:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks to me that a fix has been applied and this is therefore resolved in M4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
